From 3faaa4329d3c0083da8f0b20362dcba72263a0c9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dfattal <dfattal@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 17 Jul 2026 00:51:29 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 44/44] inline-3d(#18): 2D-over-3D via composited-layer
 resources (isolate overlay + clean SBS)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The compositing half. In the inline-3D weave config the whole page flattens into
ONE render pass (no child render passes), so an overlay can't be isolated as its
own pass. But a COMPOSITED LAYER (will-change:transform) still emits a
resource-bearing quad whose SharedImage is the element rastered on transparency
— the isolation source. This uses it to composite the overlay OVER the woven 3D
and to feed the weave CLEAN SBS, giving true 2D-over-3D (final = plate +
(1-plate.a)*woven) with a translucent overlay revealing the woven 3D underneath.
Entirely browser-side; no runtime/DP change.

- Plumb inline_3d_exclusion_rects (overlay rects) alongside inline_3d_rects
  (canvas rects) renderer -> CompositorFrameMetadata (+mojom/traits) -> Viz
  (commit_state, layer_context, layer_tree_impl/host_impl, TreesInViz).
- SurfaceAggregator: record every ROOT resource-bearing quad {parent ResourceId,
  root-space rect} (root-space = SQS quad_to_target_transform then
  transform_to_root_target); match against exclusion rects -> overlay resources,
  canvas rects -> canvas resources -> AggregatedFrame::inline_3d_{overlays,
  canvas_resources}.
- Display resolves each ResourceId -> SharedImage mailbox
  (DisplayResourceProvider::GetMailbox); hands the GPU stage {mailbox, rect}.
- WeaveCompositedSurface: source the weave INPUT from the matched canvas-layer
  resource (clean SBS, no overlay) instead of the composited output sub-rect
  (falls back to output when unmatched) -> the runtime weaves clean 3D; then
  composite each overlay resource kSrcOver the woven output.

Replaces the exclusion-hole and render-pass approaches (both dead: the hole
showed raw SBS under a translucent overlay; render passes don't exist here).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
